	<td bgcolor="#DFDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b>How to Apply</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><font color="red"><b>Warning: We look beyond level and equipment to select exceptional players.</b></font><br />
<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<b>Requirements</b><br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
We're looking for people who know their class really well, have a sense of humor, are good at communicating with others, want more out of the game than just another zerg raid, and who have the patience to help us grow the guild. We're recruiting players between levels 46 and 60 who possess a key to either Charassis (Howling Stones), Old Sebilis, or Marauder's Mire and who are on Stormhammer for the long term. <br />
<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<b>Application Form</b><br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
<ol><br />
<li>Name, Level, Race, Class:<br />
<li><a href="http://www.magelo.com">Magelo</a> Profile URL: <br />
<li>Tradeskills and levels:<br />
<li>Zone Keys held:<br />
<li>Timezone:<br />
<li>Hours you generally play / hours per week:<br />
<li>Unbuffed Magic Resistance:<br />
	Unbuffed Cold Resistance:<br />
	Unbuffed Fire Resistance:<br />
	Unbuffed Poison Resistance:<br />
	Unbuffed Disease Resistance:<br />
<li>Do you have a permanent enduring breath item?<br />
<li>Do you have an instant-buff item that works indoors? (Note -- the item must have a cast time of ZERO. If you do not have an item, you should consider getting a shrunken goblin skull earring.)<br />
<li>Do you have an instant-buff item that works outdoors?<br />
<li>Where are you in your epic quest?<br />
<li>What are you looking for in a guild? If you are currently in a guild or just left one, why are/were you dissatisfied?<br />
<li>What is your biggest pet peeve about previous guilds that you have been in?<br />
<li>What is Soylent Green?<br />
<li>Who runs Bartertown?<br />
<li>Which server do you come from? Why did you make the move to Stormhammer? What is your time-frame for moving back to that server, if at all?</li><br />
<li>Ender Wiggins, Paul Atreides, Harry Potter or Holden Caulfield?<br />
<li>Star Wars or Star Trek?<br />
<li>Fried, Steamed, Baked or Raw?<br />
<li>There is a hole with a ball in it. You have a stick. How many ways can you think of to get the ball out of the hole? List them. (The sizes of the stick, ball and hole are unspecified -- you are free to make whatever assumptions you like about their dimensions and construction.)<br />
<li>What are your goals for your character in the next 12 months?<br />
<li>The test of knowledge: To demonstrate that you know your class well, you choose ONE of the following three tasks. <br />
<br />
<b>(Option A)</b> Post a class-specific "guide" to a class board. For instance, monks might post a "Guide to Pulling Kael Arena" to <a href="http://www.monkly-business.com" target="_blank">www.monkly-business.com</a>. Shaman might post a "Guide to Shaman Levelling Spots, 40 to 50" to <a href="http://www.eqshaman.com" target="_blank">www.eqshaman.com</a>, Enchanters might post a guide to "Charming Mobs for Solo XP" and so on. Once you have posted your guide, past the URL here: <br />
<br />
<b>(Option B)</b> Answer the following questions about your class <i>in detail</i> (at least two-three paragraphs per question). What is a common misconception about your class? How does your class's role change as you move from the 40s into the 50s and upper 50s? What's a bug that currently affects your class and how would you recommend that Verant fix that bug?<br />
<br />
<b>(Option C)</b> A friend of yours just purchased a high-level character of your class, and before he embarasses himself by making stupid mistakes and getting people killed, you want to get him up to speed. Put together a reading list for your friend. List <b>five</b> must-read URLs that everybody of your class should read at least once. Do NOT list general sites such as <a href="http://www.eqshaman.com." target="_blank">www.eqshaman.com.</a> List SPECIFIC links to really good threads on class message boards, guides, and so on.<br />
<br />
<li>The test of communication: We are sick of half-assed events that start an hour late and where nobody really knows what's going on. To combat this disorganization endemic amongst many guilds, we ask members to propose raids in a format that answers the big "who, what, where, when why and how" questions. We want an event proposal from you. If you're at a loss for ideas, try writing up a proposal for one of the boss mobs required for your epic. After all, you can't expect people to help you with your epic if you're not willing to tell them HOW to help! Write that proposal here: <br />
<br />
<li>The test of humor: Be creative and have fun with this one! Basically we ask you post something humorous and original. (You could perform a standup comedy routine in a busy zone, pester some granny from Witchita, Kansas for Cyber on IM, troll a message board dedicated to gardening, smurf collectibles or bridge, manipulate an EQ screenshot, or string a series of screenshots together with hilarious narrative. It's up to you.) This part is supposed to be fun and it would be really hard to fail it, so don't stress. Paste your URL / story / Joke / screenshot / whatever here: <br />
<br />
<li>Test of Strategy: Go to the online text of "The Art of War" by Sun Tzu at <a href="http://www.sonshi.com/learn.html" target="_blank">http://www.sonshi.com/learn.html</a> and select a short quote for interpretation. Select anywhere from one to four lines of text and then explain what that particular snippet of text means in the context of the Everquest experience on Legends. Post your quote and your interpretation here:<br />
<br />
<li>Test of Patience: After you've completed your application we'll move it to a private forum for discussion. We'll generally try to post  a decision within one week, so please be patient while we discuss your app.<br />
<br />
</ol><br />
<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<b>How We Decide on Your App</b><br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
Applications are reviewed by taking into account two factors, both equally weighted. These factors are:<br />
<br />
1. <b>Strength of online application.</b> We expect top applicants to put forth a good deal of effort in completing the application to demonstrate to us their knowledge of their chosen class, their concepts of teamplay, and that they can have fun with it. If you find yourself bogged down while completing the application, having no fun, and cursing at your computer screen, then we suggest that perhaps this isn't the guild for you. We can tell when an application has been hastily written, and sloppily completed.<br />
<br />
2. <b>Personal recommendations from current guild members.</b> It is <b>your</b> responsibility, once your application is submitted (and ideally before), to actively seek out SoW members for experience groups. We are delighted to send out your LFG over guildchat, and to include you on our raids when they arise. Join our raid channel even if you are not able to make it on the raid to get a feel for how our raids are run (just communicate in tells if you have to). <br />
<br />
We balance these factors when making the decisions to admit at the beginning of each month. It is unlikely that you will gain admission, even with a brilliant application, if you have never grouped with us. It is equally unlikely that you will gain a place in the class even with several recommendations if your application is substandard. <br />
<br />
In short: we want to meet you in-game, too! It is only then that you will discover why my wife thinks I'm crazy for laughing at my computer monitor at night.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
