	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b>sample application</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>This is a sample application posted by Camthorn. It does a good job of illustrating a complete and thorough application.</b><br />
<hr><br />
<br />
No, this is not a real application, but I think this app is interesting enough to fill out just for giggles.  <br />
<br />
<b>Name:</b> Camthorn<br />
<b>Race:</b> Human<br />
<b>Class:</b> Monk<br />
<b>Level:</b> 42<br />
<b>Magelo Link:</b> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96861" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96861</a><br />
<b>Tradeskills and levels:</b> I'm a tradeskill junkie and given my low Int/Wis even the moderate levels I've attained in the arts I consider an accomplishment.<br />
Baking - 118(I make my own fish rolls!)<br />
Brewing - 46(high enough for Heady Kiolas for cured silk, probably won't take much higher until ready for Coldain Rings)<br />
Tailoring - 50(keep getting in a bind for cash and selling off all the silks I collect while hunting, doh!)<br />
Fishing - 61 (and a lot of beer went into this one I can tell you!)<br />
Planning on starting work on smithing so I can make Antonian Javelins with human cultural smithing. Need 118 skill.<br />
<br />
<b>Zone Keys held:</b> Think I've got a splintered wooden key around here somewhere.<br />
<br />
<b>Timezone:</b> Central, US<br />
<br />
<b>What times are you generally available to play?</b> None.  I'm a father of three and expecting our fourth.  My play times are extremely erratic.  <br />
<br />
<b>Unbuffed Magic Resistance:</b> 25<br />
<b>Unbuffed Cold Resistance:</b> 50<br />
<b>Unbuffed Fire Resistance:</b> 53<br />
<b>Unbuffed Poison Resistance:</b> 15<br />
<b>Unbuffed Disease Resistance:</b> 15<br />
<br />
<b>Do you have a permanent enduring breath item?</b> I have stacks of fish scales left over from fishing sessions, do those count?<br />
<br />
<b>Do you have an instant-buff item that works indoors?</b> Nope. Stupid Goblin Earring Camp kicked my butt.  That goblin pit fighter has a nasty DoT.  2hp/tick lasts FOREVER.  I feigned and went AFK about two hours after getting dotted to deal with bathing the kids and when I came back that damn owl in Firona Vie was taunting me.  I died in a newbie zone.  Not only that, I scrolled up and some newbies had tried to help me, but since I was AFK they didn't know what they could do to help.  People probably think I died to a decaying skeleton <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
<b>Do you have an instant-buff item that works outdoors?</b> See above.<br />
<br />
<b>Where are you in your epic quest?</b> I have the Red Sash of Order and I'm scouring the Karanas for those damn gnolls for the red headband. I got one of them, need two more.  I've got most of the pieces I need for the purple headband. The gnolls are really the hard part.  Then I've got the Raster and Targin camps, then the Chardok and Karnor's camps, then the four big fights.<br />
<br />
<b>What are you looking for in a guild?</b> To never have to type /lfg on ever, ever agin.<br />
<br />
<b>What is Soylent Green?</b> Lots of opinions on this, but I think it's yummy.<br />
<br />
<b>Who runs Bartertown?</b> This reference is unknown to me.  Never seen the show/read the book/heard the joke so I'll just say that Bartertown is yummy too.<br />
<br />
<b>There is a hole with a ball in it. You have a stick. How many ways can you think of to get the ball out of the hole? List them. (The sizes of the stick, ball and hole are unspecified -- you are free to make whatever assumptions you like about their dimensions and construction.) </b><br />
<br />
Heh, this is the fun one.  Can you think outside the box?  <br />
<br />
First, the classic "outside the box" solution. I say the hole is very shallow, about the size of a golf hole, and the ball is about the size of a golf ball. I pick up the ball with my hand.  Then I toss the ball in the air and bat it with the stick.<br />
<br />
Secondly.  The hole is fairly deep and in soil that is very rocky.  I gently nudge small rocks out of the sides of the hole one by one so they fall to the bottom.  Very much like the crow filling the pitcher with pebbles to drink the water, the large ball is displaced by the small rocks and it rises, eventually, to the top of the hole.  I can prod the ball if necessary to make the rocks shift and settle under it.  Then, after it has been raised enough, I pick the ball up toss the ball in the air and bat it with the stick.<br />
<br />
Thirdly.  The ball is lightweight and made of a rubbery substance and is just out of arm's reach in the hole.  The stick is a piece of PVC piping.  I place one end of the stick firmly against the surface of the ball and apply suction to the upper end, forming a vacuum inside the pipe.  Then slowly stand up and draw the ball out of the hole.  I pick the ball up toss the ball in the air and bat it with the stick.<br />
<br />
Fourthly.  The "stick" is a piece of semi-rigid PVC piping and the hole is a watertight.  Find a source of liquid and fill the hole with the liquid until the ball floats. Depending on available choices of liquid, either pick the ball up toss the ball in the air and bat it with the stick, or prod it off the top of the liquid onto firm ground and walk away.  There are some choices of liquid that I just wouldn't touch something after it's been in <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Fifthly.  This is a cheap shot, but hey I had a minor in mathematics.  I define the size of the ball to be infinite and the size of the hole to be finite.  Taking the limit of this system we see that the ball is the only thing that matters and the hole is irrelevant.  Why are you bothering me with trivialities?  I bat the ball with the stick. The gravitational pull from the infinitely large ball sucked the stick into it and then collapsed into a black hole. D'oh!  <br />
<br />
<b>If your character had a theme song that played as you went about conducting your business in Everquest, what would it be?</b><br />
<br />
Heh, I'm a monk.  My theme song would have to be the theme from M*A*S*H.  "Suicide is painless"  as in  "I have overpulled. I am going to die.  Do not attempt to heal me.  This is a recording."<br />
<br />
<b>What are your goals for your character in the next 12 months?</b><br />
<br />
To get 43!  And a haste item of some sort.  Oh, and to finally be able to eat my own cooking.<br />
<br />
<b>Test of Knowledge URL:</b> Wrote a guide to Feign Death for Monkly-Business.   <a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessage?topicID=668.topic" target="_blank">http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybus...picID=668.topic</a>  I've also contributed to a money-making guide, several pulling guides and equipment tips.<br />
<br />
<b>Test of Humor URL/Proof:</b> <br />
<a href="http://www.scienceofwar.com/forums/showthread.php?postid=183#post183" target="_blank">Here is a sample of my sense of humor</a> <br />
<br />
<b>Test of Communication:</b><br />
<br />
<font color="red">RAID CRUSHBONE!</font> <br />
<br />
Ok, need about 42-48 players to take this zone, it's horribly unbalanced.  Level ranges on the mobs run from level 4 to level 25 or so with the top creature in the zone, Ambassador D'vinn, being a HORRIBLE UNDERCON.  Our goal is Ambassador D'vinn's Black Heart. <br />
<br />
All players should be between levels 1 and 4 with basic newbie gear. Newbie tunics and rusty weapons.  If you can get a scythe or worn great staff off one of the mobs in the zone and you can use it then by all means do so.<br />
<br />
Everyone bind in Greater Faydark just outside the zone line.  We will have two dedicated pull groups.  These will be comprised of the players with the most HP.  We will pull using "Superior Feign Death" to tag pull the named mobs and split them.  <br />
<br />
Upon zone in we will clear the Orc Centurions at the entrance and set two groups to be the "wanderer" clearers.  This should leave three to four groups to be the "killer" groups.  During time periods of no wanderers the "wanderer" clearer groups should mem any spells they have and heal or give support damage to the fighting groups.  During the fights the pull groups will be on CR and scouting for the next pull.<br />
<br />
The basic path we will take is to the right of the entrance, around the "trainer hill" and across the bridge into the citadel.  We will pull back to the clear spot almost directly in front of zone in, to the immdiate south west of the trainer hill.  This gives us close proximity to the zone, not so we can run, but so those who are bound at the zone line can re-join us as soon as possible.  <br />
<br />
The key to success in this raid is the pull groups.  With careful aggro radius management it will be possible to single pull the mobs guarding the citadel, then the orc emissaries, the prophet or Emperor Crush and finally D'vinn.  Each tagger in the chain will use rusty weapons or spells to tag with depending on their class.  The primary puller will be the person with the most HP.(maybe an Ogre with all their points put into sta).  Each puller will move to their designated spot if they have multiples on them, or as far as possible before dying if they have singles.  Once a puller dies, the next puller will move into position to tag the mobs once they split to wander back to spawn points.  Using this method of splitting we should be able to hold single pull all the named mobs from the throne room.  A quick kill rate is imperative, don't go for fast damage weapons, go for high damage weapons.  At these levels, fighting mobs that are much higher level than you and without strong healing/buffing spells to back us up, any tank won't last long. Make your hit count and start running back to fight again as soon as you respawn. <br />
<br />
On bigger mobs casters are to melee and use DD ONLY. No debuffs(will probably be resisted) and no heals.  No tank will live a significant amount longer regardless of the heals.  Buffing will only be done in downtime and only by the pull groups because the fighting groups will need their mana.  The pull groups will probably die on every pull so their mana is expendable.<br />
<br />
<b>Test of Strategy:</b><br />
<br />
"One bushel of the enemy's grain is worth 20 of our own."  <br />
<br />
I wield a Guard Captian's Mallet.  I took it from a named Sarnak in Chardok after I had slain him.  Much of my equipment came from mobs, not something I produced myself.  In this way I am using the resources my enemy provides to fortify myself and to defeat further enemies.<br />
<br />
<br />
Steven</font></p>
	
